cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new approach to overcome the small sample size problem, which involves learning a discriminative null space. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), multimedia (cs.MM), information retrieval (cs.IR), and cryptography and security (cs.CR), as these areas often deal with similar issues of dimensionality reduction and feature extraction.
